Hi! I'm John Zachary N. Gillana, I'm currently a 2nd-year Bachelor of Science in Computer Engineering (BSCpE) student with a passion for building innovative software and exploring the intersections of hardware and technology. I enjoy solving real-world problems through coding, and I'm particularly interested in artificial intelligence, embedded systems, and full-stack development.
So far, I've worked on projects involving chatbot development, plant care automation, and various C# WinForms applications. I'm always excited to learn new things—whether it's a new programming language, a development framework, or diving into how things work under the hood.
When I'm not coding, you'll probably find me playing Monoposto, watching tech or racing videos, or experimenting with cool features for my current projects.
Let’s grow, build, and innovate together!
